gomodel:SYNGO_4205  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 4 shows that Mover knockdown increases the vesicular release probability, resulting in an increased and accelerated short-term depression, whereas release-ready pool size and synaptic vesicle replenishment are not altered.\nFig. 6 confirms by presynaptic capacitance recordings an increased vesicular release probability after knockdown of Mover.\n\n28/01/2021 Dnyanada: The term \"regulation of...\" was used for this annotation as the knockdown of Mover does not completely abrogate the effect on presynaptic synaptic vesicle release.. Experimental description: Sprague Dawly rats were injected with AAV particles into the VCN at P2 as described earlier (p. 530; Exp. Procedues). P12/P13 rats previously injected with AAV particles ... (p. 530)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4205" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

